data.content:
noun
[count] the sound made by something that is moving quickly - usually singular
The ball flew by with a whoosh.
a small amount of gas, liquid, etc., that comes from a place quickly - usually singular
A whoosh of hot air escaped from the vent.
verb
whooshes; whooshed; whooshing
[no obj] :to move very quickly with the sound of quickly flowing air or water
Cars whooshed along the highway.
Water whooshed down the pipe.
